			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I did :!
<br />

<br />
I a good email; well informed and good suggestions. Let me know if they do answer, I'd be eager to see what they say. It's true that the main problem is no-one really knows what this pet's role is supposed to be. 
<br />

<br />
Another option you didn't add would be giving the fire pet a short duration/frequent procing slow (not consistant with the fire pet "feel") which would now allow you to solo (because of the short duration, you couldn't slow, reclaim and bring out a tanking pet, and the fire pet cant tank for itself) and this would add significant power to the mages non-damage role in groups. I don't like my proposed solution however, because why would a fire pet slow a monster? Doesn't hold to the other pet's procs, which make sense. Anyway its still something that, for power, would be worth seeing.<br />_________________<br />"The ability to quote is a serviceable substitute for wit."
<br />
-- George Bernard Shaw (1856 - 1950)
<br />

