				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The problem I've discovered with the fire pets is more a case of the difficulty in making such creatures potent enough to do damage yet weak enough not to overpower the class they're with.
<br />

<br />
The other problem is that SoE is lazy. The Child of Ro pet is a direct copy of the GVoc Fire pet, except it doesn't nuke anymore that I've seen. It's mana pool is substandard, it's combat regen rate is pathetic, and it's melee is crippled, something that caster NPC's aren't caught with as they're SUPPOSED to be hard.
<br />

<br />
Balancing something like this is hard, but it's glaringly obvious to me that it wasn't even looked at.
<br />

<br />
Frankly, for me, I don't mind the fire pet being a wizard. In fact, I prefer the versitility it offers. Imagine bane-only mobs back in the day that couldn't be hit by pets. A damage dealing wizard pet negates this limit as it is striking with magic, just like it's master and the rest of the damage support team. Lacking this, we're just screwed missing an alternate method to deal damage through our pet, as all other pets generate damage via melee.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
