				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I can only support this email. Its pretty clear that mages in PoP are supposed to be damage dealers, and for this give up our ability to solo. So ALL of our pets should support us with this role, and frankly the fire pets dont.
<br />

<br />
My favourite solution would be to have the 50+ fire pets turned back to the old warrior class they were pre 50, with strong DS and the DD they had. However I can see that this might make them too powerful especially through the 50s. Isnt it so that most mages made the 44 and 49 fire pets their main soloing tools? That is because they did so much damage, through their DS and DD spell.
<br />

<br />
So, maybe there has to be a hard cap on the innate DS, however coupled with a slight increase in hitpoints to make up for the loss of offensive power (when the pet is tanking).
<br />

<br />
Its certainly not easy to balance this, but it would make the mage class more complete after lvl 50.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=423546" target="_blank" class="postlink">Izudin</a>, 65 Arch Convoker on Quellious</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
